    <title>Re: AC cap</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&amp;message.id=6244</link>
    <description>&lt;div&gt;I'm with Terry, here. Work on maxing Agility, Dodge, Defense, Spell Casting Subtlety, your Dodge AAs (at least through Lightning Reflexes, as the effect of RM and Precog are a great deal less per point, and more expensive to boot), and obtaining an Improved Dodge item to maximize your ability to not get hit at all, then work on Mitigation (you have to be able to survive getting hit for Natural Durability, stun resist and channelling to even matter), and then Channelling and Stun Resist. Of course, you should always work on hps via Stamina and gear, as well as Eldritch/Shadow Rune AAs.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Using the above plan, I've improved my ability to survive in relevant grouping content by a surprising amount. I don't get slaughtered anywhere near as often as I used to on aggro.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;But, with AC being so vague (it's actually two values: avoidance AC and mitigation AC), it's best to just not worry about AC at all directly, and just be glad for what you get as you accumulate better gear. Of course, if you're in the high end game and have nothing better to worry about, I guess that would be different... but, just by working on the above plan, I already have almost 900 AC unbuffed without even worrying about it, and I'm just an enthusiastic casual player.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
