    <item>
      <title>Re: AC cap</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&amp;message.id=6213#M6213</link>
      <description>I found &lt;a target="_blank" href="http://www.evilgamer.net/forums/showthread.php?t=155"&gt;this post&lt;/a&gt; on the Shadowknight forums.  It indicates that for an SK with max mitigation AAs, the AC softcap (I.e. the point where AC starts being worth less per point.) is about 500 worn, or about 1260 displayed AC.  After that, on level 70 content, a lowball estimate of the &amp;quot;diminishing returns against content&amp;quot; pont is about 2300 displayed AC. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What this means for us is:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;A) our AC softcap for displayed AC is probably below 1000.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;B) We're never going to get to the AC softcap of diminishing returns vs content, because A) I doubt there are any enchanters out there with 2300 displayed AC, and even if there are, our point of diminishing returns is -higher- because our return over softcap A is lower.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;So. Basically, don't concern yourself with AC except on your shield.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
